stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> Computed
  Computed --> Planned: lifecycle plan created
  Planned --> WrittenUnverified: governed write applied
  WrittenUnverified --> Accepted: validation, reproducibility and gates pass

  Computed --> Rejected: renderer or contract validation fails
  Planned --> Rejected: plan becomes stale or unauthorized
  WrittenUnverified --> Rejected: post-write validation or gate fails

  Rejected --> Computed: regenerate from authoritative sources
  Accepted --> Computed: source, target, base or contract drift requires refresh

  note right of Computed
    In-memory bytes only.
    Not accepted repository state.
  end note

  note right of Planned
    Evidence of intended mutation.
    No write authority granted by the plan itself.
  end note

  note right of WrittenUnverified
    Bytes exist in a governed workspace.
    Consumers MUST NOT treat them as accepted state.
  end note

  note right of Accepted
    Consumer trust boundary crossed only after
    required lifecycle validation and gates.
  end note
